                            <comment id="14949093" author="markrmiller@gmail.com" created="Thu, 8 Oct 2015 18:24:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This patch uses the client to determine safe mode rather than trying to decipher remote exceptions. I found this via what Hbase does to handle the same issue.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14949158" author="markrmiller@gmail.com" created="Thu, 8 Oct 2015 18:56:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ll commit this shortly, &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=mdrob&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;mdrob&quot;&gt;mdrob&lt;/a&gt; has already taken a look at it for me and pointed out I was missing passing a &apos;true&apos; param on checking if we were in safe mode. Mistranslation when taking it from reflection compatibility code.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve also heavily tested manually entering and exiting safe mode pretty heavily. It&apos;s much more difficult to simulate a natural safe mode situation. Given Hbase uses the code and has for a long time and the difference in using a proper (though odd), client side API (unlike the current method that depends on catching exceptions passed through a remote class), we can expect that if it works for manual safe mode, it will work for naturally entered safe mode.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
